      "content": "yo, i'm running a detective noir rpg campaign and need some help with a scene. my player just arrived at a crime scene in a pretty rough part of the city—lots of boarded up storefronts, graffiti everywhere, mostly low-income apartments and corner stores. there was a mugging/assault at a bus stop. given the vibe of this specific neighborhood, what kind of suspect profile should the detective be looking for to keep the story realistic? like, what's the most likely type of person dwelling in that area who would pull something like this?",
